The DCI detectives have arrested a suspect of Cyber Espionage. The 52-year-old  Archibald Kalela Mwandawiro was arrested on Sunday at Milondo in Wundanyi, Taita Taveta County. The DCI said upon his arrest, devices used in the interception, access and transmission of messages to unauthorized recipients were also recovered. The George Kinoti-led directorate said while acting on intelligence, the detectives raided the suspect's house. On conducting a thorough search, they found two Global Systems for Mobile communications (GSM), one fitted with 512 sim cards,  four Internet Routers, a GSM Skyline inserted with 64 Safaricom sim cards and  25 modems.